
Overview of noun feature

The noun feature has 6 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (42) feature, characteristic -- (a prominent attribute or aspect of something; "the map showed roads and other features"; "generosity is one of his best characteristics")
2. (18) feature, lineament -- (the characteristic parts of a person's face: eyes and nose and mouth and chin; "an expression of pleasure crossed his features"; "his lineaments were very regular")
3. (2) feature, feature film -- (the principal (full-length) film in a program at a movie theater; "the feature tonight is `Casablanca'")
4. feature, feature article -- (a special or prominent article in a newspaper or magazine; "they ran a feature on retirement planning")
5. feature of speech, feature -- ((linguistics) a distinctive characteristic of a linguistic unit that serves to distinguish it from other units of the same kind)
6. feature -- (an article of merchandise that is displayed or advertised more than other articles)

Overview of verb feature

The verb feature has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (16) have, feature -- (have as a feature; "This restaurant features the most famous chefs in France")
2. (3) sport, feature, boast -- (wear or display in an ostentatious or proud manner; "she was sporting a new hat")
